        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Informative">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:No towers in range?"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:No towers in range?<span> (4, Informative)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~tibit" class="author" title="author name and user ID">tibit (1762298) </a> | about 2 months ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=5496249&cid=47609631">(#47609631)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_47609631" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Informative">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>Usually, a terrestrial phone doesn't need to do anything much to "look" for a tower, besides keeping its receiver turned on. Towers emit beacons, and if you don't hear the beacon, there's no point in you sending anything - you won't receive a reply because you don't even hear the tower's beacon.</p></div>
