        <div id="comment_body_47610977" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>At work my office was in the center of the building and we had an AT&amp;T amplifier.  When I moved to Verizon (which we didn't have an amplifier for), my phone would constantly switch between 4G/LTE, 3G, and 1X, all getting about one bar.  The Verizon phone would get burning hot and drain very fast even when not in use and no apps running (but just in the office... outside, it had about the same decent experience as the AT&amp;T phone).</p><p>I'm not going to pretend to know exactly what it is doing.  But my only hope was to put together a Tasker script to turn off the cell radios while at work; that saved the battery and required me to forward calls to my work phone.</p></div>
