            <div class="comment-body"><p>I took an unlocked Nokia 1520 from AT&amp;T, to T-Mobile, to Consumer Cellular.<br>Originally, on AT&amp;T, I could not make it through a complete day on a single charge. Took it off the charger at 4:30AM. Battery was dead by 3pm.<br>Took phone to t-mobile. Off charger at 4:30AM, phone still had a quarter charge left at 10:30PM when I plugged it back in.<br>Now on Consumer Cellular. Same phone. AT&amp;T is the service provider to Consumer Cellular. Battery is not making it through the day again.</p><p>Usage patterns are similar through all three carriers. I did not do any rigorous scientific tests on this. This is observational usage data.</p></div>
